All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AdjacencyList<V,​E>
    Two-dimensional list, each vertex corresponds to a list of vertices, adjacent to the vertex.
    AdjacencyMatrix<V,​E>
    Square matrix(vertices x vertices) of booleans, matrix element Aij contains "true" if there is edge between Vi and Vj, "false" otherwise.
    Edge<V,​E>
    Weighted edge of a graph, it contains any object and 2 vertices (source and destination vertex).
    Graph<V,​E>
    Interface of weighted oriented graph with the shortest path algorithm.
    IncidenceMatrix<V,​E>
    Matrix(vertices x edges) of Integers, matrix element Aij contains "1" if Vi is tail of Ej, Aij contains "-1" if Vi is head of Ej, "0" otherwise.
    Vertex<V>
    Vertex of a graph, it contains any object.
